Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

2pd8pp513tazwWITH runidname AS ( SELECT DISTINCT b.runid, a.jobname, a.jobtype, a.designprojectname, a.ismultiinstance FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) ), runrelatie AS ( SELECT b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent, b.runid AS runid_child, a.jobname, b.afg_runstarttimestamp FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) WHERE b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd') AND sysdate -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE VEEL!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product, COUNT(product) OVER( ORDER BY rij ) AS x FROM hierarchie_tmp1 ), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, FIRST_VALUE(product) OVER(PARTITION BY x ORDER BY rij ) AS product FROM hierarchie_tmp2 ), hierarchie_tmp4 AS ( SELECT h.rij, h.child, h.parent, h.product_level, h.product FROM hierarchie_tmp3 h INNER JOIN relatie_type_product p ON ( h.product = p.persoon ) ORDER BY rij ), hierarchie_tmp5 AS ( -- EXTRA 0 level niveau erbij. Hier gebruiken we de 0 velden die al bestaan in de gegevens. De velden waar de parent NULL is. 4xm1ruvkx3awxDECLARE job BINARY_INTEGER := :job; next_date TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :mydate; broken BOOLEAN := FALSE; job_name VARCHAR2(128) := :job_name; job_subname VARCHAR2(128) := :job_subname; job_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :job_owner; job_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :job_start; job_scheduled_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :job_scheduled_start; window_start TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :window_start; window_end TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE := :window_end; chain_id VARCHAR2(14) := :chainid; credential_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :credown; credential_name VARCHAR2(128) := :crednam; destination_owner VARCHAR2(128) := :destown; destination_name VARCHAR2(128) := :destnam; job_dest_id varchar2(14) := :jdestid; log_id number := :log_id; BEGIN DECLARE ename VARCHAR2(30); exec_task BOOLEAN; BEGIN -- c heck if tuning pack is enabled exec_task := prvt_advisor.is_pack_enabled( dbms_management_packs.TUNING_PACK); -- check if we are in a pdb, -- since auto sqltune is not run in a pdb IF (exec_task AND -- tuning pack enabled sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 0 AND -- not in non-cdb sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 1 ) THEN -- not in root exec_task := FALSE; END IF; -- execute auto sql tuning task IF (exec_task) THEN ename := dbms_sqltune.execute_tuning_task( 'SYS_AUTO_SQL_TUNING_TASK'); END IF; -- check whether we are in non-CDB or a PDB -- auto SPM evolve only runs in a non-CDB or a PDB, not the root. IF (sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') = 0 OR sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') > 2) THEN exec_task := TRUE; ELSE exec_task := FALSE; END IF; -- execute auto SPM evolve task IF (exec_task) THEN ename := dbms_spm.execute_evolve_task('SYS_AUTO_SPM_EVOLVE_TASK'); END IF; END; :mydate := next_date; IF broken THEN :b := 1; ELSE :b := 0; END IF; END;

cjf5nygc4mqkyWITH runidname AS ( SELECT DISTINCT b.runid, a.jobname, a.jobtype, a.designprojectname, a.ismultiinstance FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) ), runrelatie AS ( SELECT b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent, b.runid AS runid_child, a.jobname, b.afg_runstarttimestamp FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) WHERE b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd') AND sysdate -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE VEEL!!! AND b.controlling_runid IS NOT NULL -- voor een parent child relatie om te bepalen wat een "product" is heb je de extra rij voor product niet nodig... (deze rij word er later weer bij gefietst ), parent_child AS ( -- dit is de parent child lijst als input voor de hierarchy) SELECT runid_parent AS parent, runid_child AS child, jobname AS relatie_info FROM runrelatie ORDER BY afg_runstarttimestamp ), parent AS ( SELECT DISTINCT parent FROM parent_child ), child AS ( SELECT DISTINCT child FROM parent_child ), all_child_parent AS ( SELECT DISTINCT * FROM ( SELECT * FROM child UNION ALL SELECT * FROM parent ) ), relatie_type_tussenvorm AS ( SELECT parent AS persoon, 'Tussenvorm' AS relatie_type FROM parent INNER JOIN child ON child = parent ), relatie_type_product AS ( SELECT parent AS persoon, 'Product' AS relatie_type FROM parent LEFT JOIN child ON parent = child WHERE child IS NULL ), relatie_type_bron AS ( SELECT child AS persoon, 'Bron' AS relatie_type FROM parent right JOIN child ON parent = child WHERE parent IS NULL ), all_relatie_type AS ( SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_bron UNION ALL SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_tussenvorm UNION ALL SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_product ), hierarchie AS ( -- de hierarchie bepalen met rijnummer en level SELECT ROWNUM AS rij, child, parent, level AS product_level FROM parent_child CONNECT BY NOCYCLE PRIOR child = parent ), hierarchie_tmp1 AS ( SELECT rij, child , parent, product_level, CASE WHEN product_level = 1 THEN parent ELSE NULL END AS product FROM hierarchie ORDER BY rij ), hierarchie_tmp2 AS ( -- eerste stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product, COUNT(product) OVER( ORDER BY rij ) AS x FROM hierarchie_tmp1 ), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, FIRST_VALUE(product) OVER(PARTITION BY x ORDER BY rij ) AS product FROM hierarchie_tmp2 ), hierarchie_tmp4 AS ( SELECT h.rij, h.child, h.parent, h.product_level, h.product FROM hierarchie_tmp3 h INNER JOIN relatie_type_product p ON ( h.product = p.persoon ) ORDER BY rij ), hierarchie_tmp5 AS ( -- EXTRA 0 level niveau erbij. Hier gebruiken we de 0 velden die al bestaan in de gegevens. De velden waar de parent NULL is. DEZE MOET NOG STANDAARD LAATSTE VELD WORDEN SELECT TO_NUMBER('0') AS rij, runid AS child, runid AS parent, TO_NUMBER('0') AS product_level, runid AS product FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) WHERE b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd') AND sysdate AND b.controlling_runid IS NULL ), hierarchie_tmp6 AS ( -- de laatste hierarchie_tmp4 en hierarchie_tmp5 samenvoegen) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product FROM hierarchie_tmp4 UNION ALL SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product FROM hierarchie_tmp5 ), kerstboom AS ( SELECT h.rij, h.product AS product_id, x.jobname AS product_naam, x1.relatie_type AS product_relatie_type, h.product_level, h.parent AS parent_id, y.jobname AS parent_naam, x2.relatie_type AS parent_relatie_type, h.child AS child_id, z.jobname AS child_naam, x3.relatie_type AS child_relatie_type, z.jobtype AS child_jobtype, z.designprojectname AS child_designprojectname, z.ismultiinstance AS child_ismultiinstance FROM hierarchie_tmp6 h JOIN runidname x ON ( h.product = x.runid ) JOIN runidname y ON ( h.parent = y.runid ) JOIN runidname z ON ( h.child = z.runid ) JOIN all_relatie_type x1 ON ( h.product = x1.persoon ) JOIN all_relatie_type x2 ON ( h.parent = x2.persoon ) JOIN all_relatie_type x3 ON ( h.child = x3.persoon ) ), kerstboom_ext1 AS ( -- alle runs zijn uniek dus je hoeft per runid alle data bij te voegen en je hebt alle extra gegevens... dm9uvrrubg5kq/* SQL Analyze(2438, 1) */ WITH runidname AS ( SELECT DISTINCT b.runid, a.jobname, a.jobtype, a.designprojectname, a.ismultiinstance FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) ), runrelatie AS ( SELECT b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent, b.runid AS runid_child, a.jobname, b.afg_runstarttimestamp FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) WHERE b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd') AND sysdate -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE VEEL!!! AND b.controlling_runid IS NOT NULL -- voor een parent child relatie om te bepalen wat een "product" is heb je de extra rij voor product niet nodig... (deze rij word er later weer bij gefietst ), parent_child AS ( -- dit is de parent child lijst als input voor de hierarchy) SELECT runid_parent AS parent, runid_child AS child, jobname AS relatie_info FROM runrelatie ORDER BY afg_runstarttimestamp ), parent AS ( SELECT DISTINCT parent FROM parent_child ), child AS ( SELECT DISTINCT child FROM parent_child ), all_child_parent AS ( SELECT DISTINCT * FROM ( SELECT * FROM child UNION ALL SELECT * FROM parent ) ), relatie_type_tussenvorm AS ( SELECT parent AS persoon, 'Tussenvorm' AS relatie_type FROM parent INNER JOIN child ON child = parent ), relatie_t ype_product AS ( SELECT parent AS persoon, 'Product' AS relatie_type FROM parent LEFT JOIN child ON parent = child WHERE child IS NULL ), relatie_type_bron AS ( SELECT child AS persoon, 'Bron' AS relatie_type FROM parent right JOIN child ON parent = child WHERE parent IS NULL ), all_relatie_type AS ( SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_bron UNION ALL SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_tussenvorm UNION ALL SELECT persoon, relatie_type FROM relatie_type_product ), hierarchie AS ( -- de hierarchie bepalen met rijnummer en level SELECT ROWNUM AS rij, child, parent, level AS product_level FROM parent_child CONNECT BY NOCYCLE PRIOR child = parent ), hierarchie_tmp1 AS ( SELE CT rij, child, parent, product_level, CASE WHEN product_level = 1 THEN parent ELSE NULL END AS product FROM hierarchie ORDER BY rij ), hierarchie_tmp2 AS ( -- eerste stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product, COUNT(product) OVER( ORDER BY rij ) AS x FROM hierarchie_tmp1 ), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! ) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, FIRST_VALUE(product) OVER(PARTITION BY x ORDER BY rij ) AS product FROM hierarchie_tmp2 ), hierarchie_tmp4 AS ( SELECT h.rij, h.child, h.parent, h.product_level, h.product FROM hierarchie_tmp3 h INNER JOIN relatie_type_product p ON ( h.product = p.persoon ) ORDER BY rij ), hierarchie_tmp5 AS ( -- EXTRA 0 level niveau erbij. Hier gebruiken we de 0 velden die al bestaan in de gegevens. De velden waar de parent NULL is. DEZE MOET NOG STANDAARD LAATSTE VELD WORDEN SELECT TO_NUMBER('0') AS rij, runid AS child, runid AS parent, TO_NUMBER('0') AS product_level, runid AS product FROM int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid ) WHERE b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd') AND sysdate AND b.controlling_runid IS NULL ), hierarchie_tmp6 AS ( -- de laatste hierarchie_tmp4 en hierarchie_tmp5 samenvoegen) SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product FROM hierarchie_tmp4 UNION A LL SELECT rij, child, parent, product_level, product FROM hierarchie_tmp5 ), kerstboom AS ( SELECT h.rij, h.product AS product_id, x.jobname AS product_naam, x1.relatie_type AS product_relatie_type, h.product_level, h.parent AS parent_id, y.jobname AS parent_naam, x2.relatie_type AS parent_relatie_type, h.child AS child_id, z.jobname AS child_naam, x3.relatie_type AS child_relatie_type, z.jobtype AS child_jobtype, z.designprojectname AS child_designprojectname, z.ismultiinstance AS child_ismultiinstance FROM hierarchie_tmp6 h JOIN runidname x ON ( h.product = x.runid ) JOIN runidname y ON ( h.parent = y.runid ) JOIN runidname z ON ( h.child = z.runid ) JOIN all_relatie_type x1 ON ( h.product = x1.persoon ) JOIN all_relatie_type x2 ON ( h.parent = x2.persoon ) JOIN all_relatie_type x3 ON ( h.child = x3.persoon ) ), kerstboom_ext1 AS ( -- alle runs zijn uniek dus je hoeft per runid alle data bij te voegen en je hebt alle extra gegevens... Shared Pool Advisory

  • SP: Shared Pool Est LC: Estimated Library Cache Factr: Factor
  • Note there is often a 1:Many correlation between a single logical object in the Library Cache, and the physical number of memory objects associated with it. Therefore comparing the number of Lib Cache objects (e.g. in v$librarycache), with the number of Lib Cache Memory Objects is invalid.

/* SQL Analyze(2438,1) */ WITH runidname AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
b.runid,
a.jobname,
a.jobtype,
a.designprojectname,
a.ismultiinstance
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
), runrelatie AS (
SELECT
b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent,
b.runid             AS runid_child,
a.jobname,
b.afg_runstarttimestamp
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
WHERE
b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd')
AND sysdate    -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE
VEEL!!!
AND b.controlling_runid IS NOT NULL  -- voor een parent child relatie
om te bepalen wat een "product" is heb je de extra rij voor product
niet nodig... (deze rij word er later weer bij gefietst
), parent_child AS (  -- dit is de parent child lijst als input voor
de hierarchy)
SELECT
runid_parent AS parent,
runid_child  AS child,
jobname      AS relatie_info
FROM
runrelatie
ORDER BY
afg_runstarttimestamp
), parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
parent
FROM
parent_child
), child AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
child
FROM
parent_child
), all_child_parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
*
FROM
(
SELECT
*
FROM
child
UNION ALL
SELECT
*
FROM
parent
)
), relatie_type_tussenvorm AS (
SELECT
parent       AS persoon,
'Tussenvorm' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
INNER JOIN child ON child = parent
), relatie_type_product AS (
SELECT
parent    AS persoon,
'Product' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
LEFT JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
child IS NULL
), relatie_type_bron AS (
SELECT
child  AS persoon,
'Bron' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent right
JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
parent IS NULL
), all_relatie_type AS (
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_bron
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_tussenvorm
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_product
), hierarchie AS (   -- de hierarchie bepalen met rijnummer en level
SELECT
ROWNUM AS rij,
child,
parent,
level  AS product_level
FROM
parent_child
CONNECT BY NOCYCLE
PRIOR child = parent
), hierarchie_tmp1 AS (
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
CASE
WHEN product_level = 1 THEN
parent
ELSE
NULL
END AS product
FROM
hierarchie
ORDER BY
rij
), hierarchie_tmp2 AS ( -- eerste stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
product,
COUNT(product)
OVER(
ORDER BY
rij
) AS x
FROM
hierarchie_tmp1
), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
FIRST_VALUE(product)
OVER(PARTITION BY x
ORDER BY
rij
) AS product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp2
), hierarchie_tmp4 AS (

log_id number := :log_id;  BEGIN  DECLARE

dbms_management_packs.TUNING_PACK);

-- since auto sqltune is not run in a pdb
IF (exec_task AND -- tuning pack enabled
sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 0 AND -- not in non-cdb
sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') <> 1  ) THEN -- not in root
exec_task := FALSE;
END IF;
-- execute auto sql tuning task

ename := dbms_sqltune.execute_tuning_task(
'SYS_AUTO_SQL_TUNING_TASK');
END IF;
-- check whether we are in non-CDB or a PDB
-- auto SPM evolve only runs in a non-CDB or a PDB, not the root.
IF (sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') = 0 OR
sys_context('userenv', 'con_id') > 2) THEN
exec_task := TRUE;
ELSE
exec_task := FALSE;
END IF;
-- execute auto SPM evolve task
IF (exec_task) THEN
ename := dbms_spm.execute_evolve_task('SYS_AUTO_SPM_EVOLVE_TASK');
END IF;
END;  :mydate := next_date; IF broken THEN :b := 1; ELSE :b := 0; END
IF; END;

/* SQL Analyze(2438,1) */ WITH runidname AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
b.runid,
a.jobname,
a.jobtype,
a.designprojectname,
a.ismultiinstance
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
), runrelatie AS (
SELECT
b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent,
b.runid             AS runid_child,
a.jobname,
b.afg_runstarttimestamp
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
WHERE
b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd')
AND sysdate    -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE
VEEL!!!
AND b.controlling_runid IS NOT NULL  -- voor een parent child relatie
om te bepalen wat een "product" is heb je de extra rij voor product
niet nodig... (deze rij word er later weer bij gefietst
), parent_child AS (  -- dit is de parent child lijst als input voor
de hierarchy)
SELECT
runid_parent AS parent,
runid_child  AS child,
jobname      AS relatie_info
FROM
runrelatie
ORDER BY
afg_runstarttimestamp
), parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
parent
FROM
parent_child
), child AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
child
FROM
parent_child
), all_child_parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
*
FROM
(
SELECT
*
FROM
child
UNION ALL
SELECT
*
FROM
parent
)
), relatie_type_tussenvorm AS (
SELECT
parent       AS persoon,
'Tussenvorm' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
INNER JOIN child ON child = parent
), relatie_type_product AS (
SELECT
parent    AS persoon,
'Product' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
LEFT JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
child IS NULL
), relatie_type_bron AS (
SELECT
child  AS persoon,
'Bron' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent right
JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
parent IS NULL
), all_relatie_type AS (
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_bron
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_tussenvorm
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_product
), hierarchie AS (   -- de hierarchie bepalen met rijnummer en level
SELECT
ROWNUM AS rij,
child,
parent,
level  AS product_level
FROM
parent_child
CONNECT BY NOCYCLE
PRIOR child = parent
), hierarchie_tmp1 AS (
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
CASE
WHEN product_level = 1 THEN
parent
ELSE
NULL
END AS product
FROM
hierarchie
ORDER BY
rij
), hierarchie_tmp2 AS ( -- eerste stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
product,
COUNT(product)
OVER(
ORDER BY
rij
) AS x
FROM
hierarchie_tmp1
), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )

rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
FIRST_VALUE(product)
OVER(PARTITION BY x
ORDER BY
rij
) AS product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp2
), hierarchie_tmp4 AS (

WITH runidname AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
b.runid,
a.jobname,
a.jobtype,
a.designprojectname,
a.ismultiinstance
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
), runrelatie AS (
SELECT
b.controlling_runid AS runid_parent,
b.runid             AS runid_child,
a.jobname,
b.afg_runstarttimestamp
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
WHERE
b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-20', 'yyyy-mm-dd')
AND sysdate    -- LET OP WE GEBRUIKEN NIET ALLES ANDERS WORD HET TE
VEEL!!!
AND b.controlling_runid IS NOT NULL  -- voor een parent child relatie
om te bepalen wat een "product" is heb je de extra rij voor product
niet nodig... (deze rij word er later weer bij gefietst
), parent_child AS (  -- dit is de parent child lijst als input voor
de hierarchy)
SELECT
runid_parent AS parent,
runid_child  AS child,
jobname      AS relatie_info
FROM
runrelatie
ORDER BY
afg_runstarttimestamp
), parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
parent
FROM
parent_child
), child AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
child
FROM
parent_child
), all_child_parent AS (
SELECT DISTINCT
*
FROM
(
SELECT
*
FROM
child
UNION ALL
SELECT
*
FROM
parent
)
), relatie_type_tussenvorm AS (
SELECT
parent       AS persoon,
'Tussenvorm' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
INNER JOIN child ON child = parent
), relatie_type_product AS (
SELECT
parent    AS persoon,
'Product' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent
LEFT JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
child IS NULL
), relatie_type_bron AS (
SELECT
child  AS persoon,
'Bron' AS relatie_type
FROM
parent right
JOIN child ON parent = child
WHERE
parent IS NULL
), all_relatie_type AS (
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_bron
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_tussenvorm
UNION ALL
SELECT
persoon,
relatie_type
FROM
relatie_type_product
), hierarchie AS (   -- de hierarchie bepalen met rijnummer en level
SELECT
ROWNUM AS rij,
child,
parent,
level  AS product_level
FROM
parent_child
CONNECT BY NOCYCLE
PRIOR child = parent
), hierarchie_tmp1 AS (
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
CASE
WHEN product_level = 1 THEN
parent
ELSE
NULL
END AS product
FROM
hierarchie
ORDER BY
rij
), hierarchie_tmp2 AS ( -- eerste stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
product,
COUNT(product)
OVER(
ORDER BY
rij
) AS x
FROM
hierarchie_tmp1
), hierarchie_tmp3 AS ( -- tweede stap aanvullen prouduct veld!!! )
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
FIRST_VALUE(product)
OVER(PARTITION BY x
ORDER BY
rij
) AS product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp2
), hierarchie_tmp4 AS (
SELECT
h.rij,
h.child,
h.parent,
h.product_level,
h.product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp3 h
INNER JOIN relatie_type_product p ON ( h.product = p.persoon )
ORDER BY
rij
), hierarchie_tmp5 AS (  -- EXTRA 0 level niveau erbij. Hier
gebruiken we de 0 velden die al bestaan in de gegevens. De velden
waar de parent NULL is. DEZE MOET NOG STANDAARD LAATSTE VELD WORDEN
SELECT
TO_NUMBER('0') AS rij,
runid          AS child,
runid          AS parent,
TO_NUMBER('0') AS product_level,
runid          AS product
FROM
int_perf_np.int_jobexec_ht a
INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht b ON ( a.jobid = b.jobid )
WHERE
b.afg_runstarttimestamp BETWEEN TO_DATE('2024-01-01', 'yyyy-mm-dd')
AND sysdate
AND b.controlling_runid IS NULL
), hierarchie_tmp6 AS ( -- de laatste hierarchie_tmp4 en
hierarchie_tmp5 samenvoegen)
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp4
UNION ALL
SELECT
rij,
child,
parent,
product_level,
product
FROM
hierarchie_tmp5
), kerstboom AS (
SELECT
h.rij,
h.product           AS product_id,
x.jobname           AS product_naam,
x1.relatie_type     AS product_relatie_type,
h.product_level,
h.parent            AS parent_id,
y.jobname           AS parent_naam,
x2.relatie_type     AS parent_relatie_type,
h.child             AS child_id,
z.jobname           AS child_naam,
x3.relatie_type     AS child_relatie_type,
z.jobtype           AS child_jobtype,
z.designprojectname AS child_designprojectname,
z.ismultiinstance   AS child_ismultiinstance
FROM
hierarchie_tmp6 h
JOIN runidname        x ON ( h.product = x.runid )
JOIN runidname        y ON ( h.parent = y.runid )
JOIN runidname        z ON ( h.child = z.runid )
JOIN all_relatie_type x1 ON ( h.product = x1.persoon )
JOIN all_relatie_type x2 ON ( h.parent = x2.persoon )
JOIN all_relatie_type x3 ON ( h.child = x3.persoon )
), kerstboom_ext1 AS (  -- alle runs zijn uniek dus je hoeft per
runid alle data bij te voegen en je hebt alle extra gegevens...
MIOSSCHIEN NOG WAT EXTRA INFO ZOALS INVOCATION INFO
SELECT
k.rij,
k.product_id,
k.product_naam,
k.product_relatie_type,
k.product_level,
k.parent_id,
k.parent_naam,
k.parent_relatie_type,
k.child_id,
k.child_naam,
k.child_relatie_type,
k.child_jobtype,
k.child_designprojectname,
k.child_ismultiinstance,
r.invocationid,
r.runstarttimestamp,
r.runendtimestamp,
r.afg_runstarttimestamp,
r.afg_runendtimestamp,
r.runtype,
r.runmajorstatus,
r.runminorstatus,
r.elapsedrunsecs,
r.totalrowsconsumed,
r.totalrowsproduced,
r.totalcpu
FROM

INNER JOIN int_perf_np.int_jobrun_ht r ON ( k.child_id = r.runid )
), run_start_end_1 AS ( -- alle kerstboomen de start en eind in 2
regels stoppen!! Deze heeft de start
SELECT
rij,

elapsedrunsecs,
totalrowsconsumed,
totalrowsproduced,
totalcpu,
afg_runstarttimestamp AS run_startend,
'start'               AS startstop,
1                     AS verander
FROM
kerstboom_ext1
), run_start_end_2 AS ( -- alle kerstboomen de start en eind in 2
regels stoppen!! Deze heeft de stop
SELECT
rij,
product_id,
product_naam,
product_relatie_type,
product_level,
parent_id,
parent_naam,
parent_relatie_type,
child_id,
child_naam,
child_relatie_type,
child_jobtype,
child_designprojectname,
child_ismultiinstance,
invocationid,
runstarttimestamp,
runendtimestamp,
runtype,
runmajorstatus,
runminorstatus,
elapsedrunsecs,
totalrowsconsumed,
totalrowsproduced,
totalcpu,
afg_runendtimestamp AS run_startend,
'stop'              AS startstop,
- 1                 AS verander
FROM
kerstboom_ext1
), run_start_end_all AS ( -- DIT IS DE BASIS, VANAF HIER ALLEEN NOG
EXTRA SOMMATIES BIJVOEGEN OP VERSCHILLENDE NIVEAUS..
SELECT
*
FROM
run_start_end_1
UNION ALL
SELECT
*
FROM
run_start_end_2
), sum_all AS ( -- 3.  som aantal draaiende jobs op alles geordenend
naar tijd (dus over de modules heen)
SELECT
rij,
product_id,
product_naam,
product_relatie_type,
product_level,
parent_id,
parent_naam,
parent_relatie_type,
child_id,
child_naam,
child_relatie_type,
child_jobtype,
child_designprojectname,
child_ismultiinstance,
invocationid,
runstarttimestamp,
runendtimestamp,
runtype,
runmajorstatus,
runminorstatus,
elapsedrunsecs,
totalrowsconsumed,
totalrowsproduced,
totalcpu,
run_startend,
startstop,
SUM(verander)
OVER(
ORDER BY

ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
) aantaljobs
FROM

), sum_all_par AS ( -- 4.  som aantal draaiende parrelel en server
jobs op alles geordenend naar tijd (dus over de modules heen)
SELECT
rij,
product_id,
product_naam,
product_relatie_type,

elapsedrunsecs,

totalrowsproduced,
totalcpu,

SUM(verander)
OVER(

ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
) aantaljobs_par
FROM

WHERE

ORDER BY

), sum_all_par_1 AS ( --  3 en 4 samen versie 1
SELECT
a.rij,
a.product_id,
a.product_naam,
a.product_relatie_type,
a.product_level,
a.parent_id,
a.parent_naam,
a.parent_relatie_type,

a.elapsedrunsecs,

a.totalrowsproduced,
a.totalcpu,
a.run_startend,
a.startstop,
a.aantaljobs,
b.aantaljobs_par,
COUNT(aantaljobs_par)
OVER(
ORDER BY
a.run_startend, a.startstop
) AS x
FROM
sum_all     a
LEFT OUTER JOIN sum_all_par b ON ( a.child_id = b.child_id )
AND ( a.startstop = b.startstop )
ORDER BY
a.run_startend,
a.startstop
), sum_all_par_final AS (-- 3 en 4 samen en null gevuld
SELECT
a.rij,
a.product_id,
a.product_naam,
a.product_relatie_type,
a.product_level,
a.parent_id,
a.parent_naam,
a.parent_relatie_type,

a.totalrowsproduced,
a.totalcpu,
a.run_startend,
a.startstop,
a.aantaljobs,
FIRST_VALUE(aantaljobs_par)
OVER(PARTITION BY x
ORDER BY
a.run_startend, a.startstop
